{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/flyhud\/best-practices"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD"]]},"metadata":{"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"Best Practices","modules":[{"name":"FlyHUD"}]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Lifecycle Management","anchor":"Lifecycle-Management","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following diagram shows the recommended pattern for managing HUD lifecycle with async operations:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"best-practices-lifecycle.svg"}]},{"text":"Always Hide Your HUDs","anchor":"Always-Hide-Your-HUDs","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensure every "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"show()"},{"type":"text","text":" has a matching "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hide()"},{"type":"text","text":" to prevent leaked HUD views:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let hud = HUD.show(to: view)","","Task {","    do {","        let result = try await fetchData()","        hud.contentView.mode = .custom(UIImageView(image: UIImage(systemName: \"checkmark\")))","        hud.contentView.label.text = \"Done\"","        hud.hide(afterDelay: 1.0)","    } catch {","        hud.contentView.mode = .text","        hud.contentView.label.text = \"Failed\"","        hud.hide(afterDelay: 2.0)","    }","}"]},{"text":"Use removeFromSuperViewOnHide","anchor":"Use-removeFromSuperViewOnHide","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HUD.show(to:)"},{"type":"text","text":", the HUD is automatically removed from its superview"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on hide (default behavior). For manually created HUDs, set this explicitly:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let hud = HUD(with: view)","hud.removeFromSuperViewOnHide = true","view.addSubview(hud)","hud.show()"]},{"text":"Avoid Retain Cycles","anchor":"Avoid-Retain-Cycles","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[weak self]"},{"type":"text","text":" when referencing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"self"},{"type":"text","text":" in completion blocks:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["hud.completionBlock = { [weak self] _ in","    self?.navigateToNextScreen()","}"]},{"text":"View Hierarchy","anchor":"View-Hierarchy","type":"heading","level":2},{"text":"Choose the Right Parent View","anchor":"Choose-the-Right-Parent-View","type":"heading","level":3},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Good: Add to the view controller's view","HUD.show(to: self.view)","","\/\/ Good: Add to a specific container","HUD.show(to: tableView)","","\/\/ Caution: Adding to window covers everything","HUD.show(to: view.window!)"]},{"text":"Avoid Adding to Scrollable Views","anchor":"Avoid-Adding-to-Scrollable-Views","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Adding a HUD to a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIScrollView"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UITableView"},{"type":"text","text":" directly may cause"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unexpected behavior as the user scrolls. Prefer adding to the view controller’s view."}]},{"text":"Async\/Await Integration","anchor":"AsyncAwait-Integration","type":"heading","level":2},{"text":"With Swift Concurrency","anchor":"With-Swift-Concurrency","type":"heading","level":3},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@MainActor","func loadData() async {","    let hud = HUD.show(to: view)","","    do {","        let data = try await api.fetchItems()","        updateUI(with: data)","    } catch {","        showError(error)","    }","","    hud.hide()","}"]},{"text":"With URLSession","anchor":"With-URLSession","type":"heading","level":3},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let hud = HUD.show(to: view, mode: .progress(.roundBar), label: \"Downloading\")","","let observation = task.progress.observe(\\.fractionCompleted) { progress, _ in","    DispatchQueue.main.async {","        hud.contentView.progress = Float(progress.fractionCompleted)","    }","}","","\/\/ Or use observedProgress for automatic binding","hud.contentView.observedProgress = task.progress"]},{"text":"Grace Time Usage","anchor":"Grace-Time-Usage","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use grace time to avoid HUD flicker for fast operations:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let hud = HUD(with: view)","hud.graceTime = 0.3          \/\/ Don't show for tasks < 300ms","hud.minShowTime = 0.5        \/\/ If shown, display for at least 500ms","hud.removeFromSuperViewOnHide = true","view.addSubview(hud)","hud.show()","","\/\/ Fast task — HUD never appears","DispatchQueue.main.asyncAfter(deadline: .now() + 0.1) {","    hud.hide()","}"]},{"text":"Activity Count Pattern","anchor":"Activity-Count-Pattern","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use activity counts for multi-source loading states:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["class DataManager {","    private var hud: HUD?","","    func showLoading(on view: UIView) {","        if hud == nil {","            hud = HUD.show(to: view)","            hud?.isCountEnabled = true","        } else {","            hud?.show()","        }","    }","","    func hideLoading() {","        hud?.hide()","    }","}"]},{"text":"Performance","anchor":"Performance","type":"heading","level":2},{"text":"Reuse HUD Instances","anchor":"Reuse-HUD-Instances","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For repeated show\/hide cycles, reuse the same HUD instance:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["class ViewController: UIViewController {","    private lazy var hud: HUD = {","        let hud = HUD(with: view)","        hud.removeFromSuperViewOnHide = false","        view.addSubview(hud)","        return hud","    }()","","    func refresh() {","        hud.show()","        \/\/ ...","        hud.hide()","    }","}"]},{"text":"Avoid Unnecessary Mode Changes","anchor":"Avoid-Unnecessary-Mode-Changes","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Changing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"mode"},{"type":"text","text":" tears down and rebuilds indicator views. Only change when needed:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Avoid in tight loops","\/\/ ❌ hud.contentView.mode = .indicator(.large)  \/\/ every frame","","\/\/ ✅ Set once, update progress\/labels as needed","hud.contentView.progress = newValue"]},{"text":"Error Handling Pattern","anchor":"Error-Handling-Pattern","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"error-handling-states.svg"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Transition HUD state on success\/failure:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let hud = HUD.show(to: view, label: \"Saving...\")","","saveDocument { result in","    switch result {","    case .success:","        let checkmark = UIImageView(image: UIImage(systemName: \"checkmark\"))","        hud.contentView.mode = .custom(checkmark)","        hud.contentView.label.text = \"Saved\"","        hud.hide(afterDelay: 1.5)","","    case .failure(let error):","        hud.contentView.mode = .text","        hud.contentView.label.text = \"Error\"","        hud.contentView.detailsLabel.text = error.localizedDescription","        hud.hide(afterDelay: 3.0)","    }","}"]},{"text":"Accessibility","anchor":"Accessibility","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"FlyHUD provides comprehensive VoiceOver and accessibility support out of the box."}]},{"text":"VoiceOver Architecture","anchor":"VoiceOver-Architecture","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"accessibility-architecture.svg"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"FlyHUD uses a "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"single-element","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" accessibility design:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"ContentView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is the sole VoiceOver focus element within the HUD"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All child views (labels, buttons, indicators, progress views) are hidden from accessibility"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"VoiceOver reads a combined description of labels + progress status as one coherent announcement"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Button actions are exposed via "},{"code":"accessibilityCustomActions","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (swipe up\/down to discover)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The HUD automatically manages VoiceOver focus:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ When shown:  VoiceOver focus moves to HUD (via .screenChanged notification)","\/\/ When hidden: VoiceOver focus returns to underlying content","","let hud = HUD.show(to: view, mode: .indicator(), label: \"Loading...\")","\/\/ VoiceOver announces: \"Loading...\"","","hud.contentView.detailsLabel.text = \"Please wait\"","\/\/ VoiceOver re-reads: \"Loading..., Please wait\""]},{"text":"Escape Gesture","anchor":"Escape-Gesture","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"VoiceOver users can dismiss the HUD via the standard two-finger Z-scrub (escape) gesture."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This calls "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"accessibilityPerformEscape()"},{"type":"text","text":" and hides the HUD with animation."}]},{"text":"Contextual Hints","anchor":"Contextual-Hints","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"accessibilityHint"},{"type":"text","text":" provides mode-aware context to VoiceOver users:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Indicator modes: “Loading in progress”"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Progress modes: “Task in progress”"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Text-only modes: no hint (nil)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Modal Focus Management","anchor":"Modal-Focus-Management","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"HUD sets "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"accessibilityViewIsModal = true"},{"type":"text","text":" to prevent VoiceOver from navigating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to elements behind the overlay. This is automatic — no configuration needed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isEventDeliveryEnabled = true"},{"type":"text","text":" (touches pass through), "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"accessibilityViewIsModal"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is automatically set to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":" so VoiceOver focus can reach underlying content."}]},{"text":"Progress Announcements","anchor":"Progress-Announcements","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In progress mode, VoiceOver users receive periodic updates:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"accessibilityValue","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" dynamically reports the current percentage (e.g., “45%”)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"accessibilityTraits","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" includes "},{"code":".updatesFrequently","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for progress\/indicator modes"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Milestone announcements are posted at 25% intervals (0%, 25%, 50%, 75%, 100%)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let hud = HUD.show(to: view, mode: .progress(.round), label: \"Downloading\")","\/\/ VoiceOver announces: \"Downloading\" with value \"0%\"","","hud.contentView.progress = 0.5","\/\/ VoiceOver announces: \"50%\" (milestone notification)"]},{"text":"Dynamic Type","anchor":"Dynamic-Type","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Enable Dynamic Type for HUD labels:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["hud.contentView.isDynamicTypeEnabled = true"]},{"text":"Content Color Contrast","anchor":"Content-Color-Contrast","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensure sufficient contrast between content and background:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Dark background with light text","hud.contentView.style = .solidColor","hud.contentView.color = UIColor(white: 0.1, alpha: 0.9)","hud.contentView.contentColor = .white"]},{"text":"Custom Views & Accessibility","anchor":"Custom-Views--Accessibility","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".custom(UIView)"},{"type":"text","text":" mode, set "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isAccessibilityElement = false"},{"type":"text","text":" on your custom view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to maintain the single-element pattern:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let checkmark = UIImageView(image: UIImage(systemName: \"checkmark\"))","checkmark.isAccessibilityElement = false  \/\/ Recommended","","HUD.show(to: view, mode: .custom(checkmark), label: \"Done\")","\/\/ VoiceOver announces: \"Done\" (not the image's default accessibility)"]},{"text":"Button Actions","anchor":"Button-Actions","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When a button is configured, VoiceOver exposes it via custom actions:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let hud = HUD.show(to: view, mode: .indicator(), label: \"Uploading...\")","hud.contentView.button.setTitle(\"Cancel\", for: .normal)","hud.contentView.button.addTarget(self, action: #selector(cancel), for: .touchUpInside)","\/\/ VoiceOver: Swipe up\/down to discover \"Cancel\" action"]}]}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Recommended patterns for using FlyHUD effectively in production apps.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/best-practices"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Guides","generated":true,"title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/advanced-features","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/custom-ui","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/swiftui-integration","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/testing"]}],"references":{"doc://flyhud.FlyHUD/documentation/FlyHUD/testing":{"url":"\/documentation\/flyhud\/testing","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/testing","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Strategies for unit testing, integration testing, and mocking FlyHUD in your app."}],"title":"Testing Guide","type":"topic","role":"article"},"best-practices-lifecycle.svg":{"identifier":"best-practices-lifecycle.svg","type":"image","alt":"Sequence d